OL,6,FDespite witnessing first-hand the
OL,7,F"horror and pain" that the perpetrator
OL,8,Finflicted and the fear she felt for
OL,9,Fher own life and those in the room,
OL,10,FHeidi says she was told by police that
OL,11,Fshe was no longer a victim "but simply
OL,12,Fa witness".
OL,14,FShe said: "Whilst I will always
OL,15,Fconsider other people' s experiences
OL,16,Fand feelings that day above my own,
OL,17,Fthis labelling made me feel like my
OL,18,Fown experience was immaterial, trivial
OL,19,For even worthless.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
