OL,6,F"I'm grieving for the girls and their
OL,7,Ffamilies, the girls that were there
OL,8,Fthat day, Leanne, police, responders,
OL,9,Fneighbours who opened their homes, the
OL,10,Fwider community but I'm also grieving
OL,11,Ffor the old version of myself and my
OL,12,Flife," she said.
OL,14,F"I cannot remember myself or my life
OL,15,Fbefore this. All I can remember is
OL,16,Fthis current version of things `
OL,17,Fconstantly re-living the events of the
OL,18,Fday, dealing with the overwhelming
OL,19,Femotions and fears connected."
